      <bioghist id="aspace_5aa3fa6bff47f601e972791611915ab8">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Lester Clyde Lichty earned degrees from the University of Nebraska (B.S.1913), University of Illinois (M.S. 1916), and Yale University (M.E. 1925).Â  He taught in the Yale Mechanical Engineering Department from 1923 to 1960.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_3c5010ed327bf466ba01dd67f5585b65">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The material consists of correspondence, enclosures, and reports by Lester Clyde Lichty and his assistant, James F. Swartwout, relating to internal combustion engines. Also included is a report by Howard D. Baldwin, for which Lichty conducted the analysis.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_568505079abd6b914045a4681525faef">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The material is arranged chronologically by report date.</p>  
      </arrangement>
